'''''Frederick the Great Playing the Flute at Sanssouci''''' is an 1852 oil on canvas history painting by [[Adolph Menzel]] showing [[Frederick the Great]] playing the flute at an evening concert in his palace of [[Sanssouci]]. It is now in the [[Alte Nationalgalerie]] in Berlin.

